
The best approach for new IT-based start-ups to aim both Islam and Chinese markets would be to first conduct thorough market research to understand the specific needs and preferences of these target audiences. This can include studying the cultural and religious values of Muslim consumers, as well as the technological trends and preferences of Chinese consumers. Additionally, it would be important for the start-up to partner with local businesses and influencers to gain credibility and reach in these markets. Two things to be considered would be language localization and compliance with local regulations and laws.


